KANO – A Federal High court sitting in Kano on Wednesday sentenced a 36- year- old man, Abdulkareem Yahaya Danmallam to 10 years in jail for defiling a nine-year-old primary school pupil. The court also ordered the convict to pay N1 million as fine for committing the crime. The Presiding Judge, Justice K. K.Dagat, said the convict did not deserve to live within the society. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The National Agency For the Prohibition of Trafficking in Persons (NAPTIP) had on Feburay 21 2018 dragged the convict before the court for procuring and sexually exploiting a nine-year-old girl (name withheld). According to the charge sheet number FHC/KN/CR/01/2018, the incident occurred at Gidan Dagaci located in Gwale Local Government, Kano State, North West Nigeria. The prosecutor, Barrister Abdullahi Babale, told the court that that convict lured the victim while she was on her way to school. Barister Babale informed the court that, Abdulkareem Yahya Danmallam lured his victim by offering her N10.00 and then proceeded to defile her. He further told the court that the convict acted in contrast to the provisions of the laws, punishable under section 16(1) of the trafficking in Persons Act of 2015. The prosecutor produced three witnesses, who gave testimony before the court,  and also  tendered in evidence two documents, which are  the confessional statement  made by the convict that was seconded  by a  medical report obtained from  Muritala Muhammad Specialist Hospital, Kano. Abdulkareem Yahaya Danmallam,  who denied the allegations had through his counsel, Muritala Alimi, urged the court to dismiss the allegations leveled against the defendant.